This paper discusses software engineering discipline and the progress made in the last decade, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper specifically focuses on enabling reusability in Agile Software Development, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SD (Software Development) categories. The paper may also touch upon machine learning techniques for software development, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Finally, the paper may discuss cost-effectiveness and productivity improvement, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) category.
